FSRI: Dimensions: 101.45 x 101.27 x 0.89 mm; with frame; with calcium silicate substrate

After ignition an air bubble formed beneath the sample which raised the height of the sample surface. After a few seconds a hole formed in the sample which released the gases in the bubble at high enough velocity to form a horizontal flame that extended beyond the radius of the cone. This lasted less than 5 seconds, then the sample returned to normal burning behavoir.
